messages.message: In the build process the ability to create a validation that applies to all is available and aligns with what would be common to do for model confidence checks.  However tables do not have confidence so 100% of tables fail.  Seems like the table field type should be skipped in the confidence check since it does not calculate confidence
@Elan Sharony we used to do this on the backend for reasoning fields before those provided confidence values right? do we need to make a similar fix for table fields now?
hmm yeah that sounds like the right move, especially if tables don't have confidences. Will create ticket for this!
